      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BLUE LUPIN (4) has been cruelled by wide gates and finally draws inside. Made up a stack of ground beaten 1.9L over the mile at Pinjarra second-up and Faithfull sticks aboard. Finds a suitable assignment. COSMIC GEM (5) pushed forward here last time over 1500m beaten a head. Was heavily bet, and despite the outside gate, is the key runner. TASMAN JEWEL (7) settled back in the same race, posting a distant third. Led as favourite here this trip prior and wasn't too far away. Has the blinkers on again, and we're likely to see improvement. HUNDRED YARDS (2) was in the money two starts ago at this track/trip, but couldn't back it up last time over 1600m at Pinjarra. Minor hope. Ditto GOD'LL GETYA (3), who will be fitter and he draws well for a change.",
